    "# import libraries\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency\n",
    "\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "from pandas.io.json import json_normalize\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import difflib \n",
    "import fuzzy_pandas as fpd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt \n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 467,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# data\n",
    "# our data spans from 1997 to 2020, transfer periods include winter and summer\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('jaccard_dataset_1.csv')\n",
    "#df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 468,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# change the name of columns, otherwise my codes don't work\n",
    "df = df.rename(columns={'Full nation name':'nationality','nationality':'manager_nationality','manager_name':'Manager_name'})\n",
    "''' we focus on the player moving in because the movement of manager buying the player is caused mainly by the buyer,\n",
    "if we include player moving in, then there will be overlap'''\n",
    "df_in = df.loc[df.transfer_movement=='in']\n",
    "df_in =df_in.reset_index(drop = True)\n",
    "df_in.loc[:,'count']=1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## get time and period and information for managers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 469,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# get the list for periods and years\n",
    "period=[]\n",
    "time=[]\n",
    "for year in np.arange(1997,2021):\n",
    "    for transfer_period in ['Summer','Winter']: \n",
    "        time.append(year)\n",
    "        period.append(transfer_period)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 470,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# manager information \n",
    "manager_info=df_in.groupby(['Manager_name','club_name','year','manager_nationality'])['count'].agg(np.sum).to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# purchase of clubs\n",
    "club_buy=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "club_manager=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "\n",
    "for year in np.arange(1997,2021):\n",
    "    for transfer_period in ['Summer','Winter']: \n",
    "        df_year = df_in.loc[(df_in.year==year)&(df_in.transfer_period==transfer_period)]\n",
    "        df_year = df_year.groupby(['club_name','player_name','nationality','Manager_name','manager_nationality','match'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "        df_year=df_year.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "        df_club = df_year.groupby(['club_name','Manager_name'])['count'].agg(np.sum).to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "        club_manager=pd.concat([club_manager,df_club.club_name.value_counts().to_frame().T],ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# purchase of clubs\n",
    "        club_buy=pd.concat([club_buy,df_year.club_name.value_counts().to_frame().T],ignore_index=True)\n",
    "# the maximum purchase from 1997 to 2020 for each club\n",
    "max_club_buy = club_buy.max()\n",
    "\n",
    "# max purchase within one period of each club\n",
    "for club in np.unique(manager_info.club_name):\n",
    "    manager_info.loc[manager_info.club_name==club,'max_club_buy']=max_club_buy.get(club)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# expected vs practical"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 438,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "'''the 'probability' function is biased, in the sense that it includes possibility that managers or players being isolated, \n",
    "and the possibility that same players are chosen by different managers'''\n",
    "'''Assuming that each transfer period, the managers and players in the market are fixed and only include those who appear\n",
    "in the dataset; using 1000 times random simulations, we calculate the ratios that managers chose the players\n",
    "with same nationality; and finally take the means of 1000 times simulations for each transfer period'''\n",
    "'''In each simulation, every manager has the chance to select a random number of random players while we guarantee \n",
    "that players are chosen only once'''\n",
    "# takes about 30 mins\n",
    "# set seed\n",
    "np.random.seed(000)\n",
    "expected_wo=list()\n",
    "expected_all=list()\n",
    "with_En=[]\n",
    "without=[]\n",
    "ratio_m_std=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "ratio_m_mean=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "\n",
    "# for loop for each period\n",
    "for year in np.arange(1997,2021):\n",
    "    for transfer_period in ['Summer','Winter']: \n",
    "        df_year = df_in.loc[(df_in.year==year)&(df_in.transfer_period==transfer_period)]\n",
    "        df_year = df_year.groupby(['player_name','nationality','Manager_name','manager_nationality','match'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "        df_year=df_year.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# because one player can only transfer once in each period, so the number of ties will be the same as players'\n",
    "        player = df_year[['player_name','nationality','Manager_name']]\n",
    "        player=player.reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "# to get the nodes of managers\n",
    "        manager = df_year.groupby(['Manager_name','manager_nationality'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "        manager=manager.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "# real percentage of match with England\n",
    "        with_En.append(len(np.where(df_year.match=='yes')[0])/len(df_year))\n",
    "\n",
    "        expt=[]\n",
    "        m_n = len(manager)\n",
    "        p_num=len(player)\n",
    "        ratio_m=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "        for i in range(1000):\n",
    "# the list of players in the market in number\n",
    "            player_1 = list(np.arange(p_num))\n",
    "\n",
    "            count=0\n",
    "            for m in np.arange(m_n):\n",
    "                count_m=0\n",
    "                left=len(player_1)\n",
    "# max_purchase is for the constraint of purchase limit\n",
    "                max_purchase=manager_info.loc[manager_info.Manager_name==manager.Manager_name[m]].max_club_buy.values[0]\n",
    "# another method of constraint, keeping the number of players chosen as the same of the practical one, but we are not using it\n",
    "#                 k_c= df_year[df_year.Manager_name==manager.Manager_name[m]].Manager_name.count()\n",
    "#                 choice = np.random.choice(player_1,replace=False,size=int(k_c))\n",
    "                if m == m_n-1:\n",
    "                    choice =player_1\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "# guarantee the every player is chosen and every manger can choose at least one\n",
    "                    k_c = np.random.choice(np.arange(1,min(max_purchase,left-(m_n-m-1))+1),size=1) \n",
    "# randomly choose players\n",
    "                    choice = np.random.choice(player_1,replace=False,size=int(k_c))\n",
    "# take out players from the list if being chosen\n",
    "                    for cho in choice:\n",
    "                        player_1.remove(cho)\n",
    "# if the manager and the player have same nationality, record the 'count_m'\n",
    "                for c in choice:\n",
    "                    p_n = player.nationality[c]\n",
    "                    if manager.manager_nationality[m]==p_n:\n",
    "                        count_m+=1\n",
    "                count=count+count_m\n",
    "# the ratio for each manager choosing players of same nationality\n",
    "                ratio_m.loc[i,manager.Manager_name[m]]=count_m/len(choice)\n",
    "# the ratio for each period all the managers choosing players of same nationality\n",
    "            expected_1=count/len(player.player_name)\n",
    "            expt.append(expected_1)\n",
    "# take mean and standard deviation for each manager of the 1000 times simulations and put them in a data frame\n",
    "        ratio_m_mean=pd.concat([ratio_m_mean,ratio_m.mean().to_frame().T],ignore_index=True) \n",
    "        ratio_m_std=pd.concat([ratio_m_std,ratio_m.std().to_frame().T],ignore_index=True)\n",
    "        expected_all.append(np.average(expt))\n",
    "                            \n",
    "                            \n",
    "                            \n",
    "# take out england, similar code as before, but we didn't compute ratio for each manager\n",
    "        df_year = df_year[df_year.manager_nationality!='England']\n",
    "        player = df_year[['player_name','nationality','Manager_name']]\n",
    "        player=player.reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "        manager = df_year.groupby(['Manager_name','manager_nationality'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "        manager=manager.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "# real percentage of match without England\n",
    "        without.append(len(np.where(df_year.match=='yes')[0])/len(df_year))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        expt=[]\n",
    "        m_n = len(manager)\n",
    "        p_num=len(player)\n",
    "        for i in range(1000):\n",
    "            player_1 = list(np.arange(p_num))            \n",
    "\n",
    "            count=0\n",
    "            for m in np.arange(m_n):\n",
    "                left=len(player_1)\n",
    "                max_purchase=manager_info.loc[manager_info.Manager_name==manager.Manager_name[m]].max_club_buy.values[0]\n",
    "#                 k_c= df_year[df_year.Manager_name==manager.Manager_name[m]].Manager_name.count()\n",
    "#                 choice = np.random.choice(player_1,replace=False,size=int(k_c))\n",
    "                if m == m_n-1:\n",
    "                    choice =player_1\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    k_c = np.random.choice(np.arange(1,min(max_purchase,left-(m_n-m-1))+1),size=1) \n",
    "                    choice = np.random.choice(player_1,replace=False,size=int(k_c))\n",
    "                    for cho in choice:\n",
    "                        player_1.remove(cho)\n",
    "                    #player_1 = [ele for ele in player_1 if ele not in choice]\n",
    "                for c in choice:\n",
    "                    p_n = player.nationality[c]\n",
    "                    if manager.manager_nationality[m]==p_n:\n",
    "                        count=count+1\n",
    "                    \n",
    "            expected_1=count/len(player.player_name)\n",
    "\n",
    "            expt.append(expected_1)\n",
    "            \n",
    "        expected_wo.append(np.average(expt))"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# expected / Result corresponding to managers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 472,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The practical percentage of manager choosing players from same nationality\n",
    "ratios_practical=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "managers=[]\n",
    "index=0\n",
    "for year in np.arange(min(df.year),2021):\n",
    "    for transfer_period in ['Summer','Winter']:\n",
    "        df_manager = df_in[(df_in.year==year)&(df_in.transfer_period==transfer_period)].groupby(['year','transfer_period','Manager_name','manager_nationality','player_name','nationality','match'])['count'].sum().to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "        for manager in np.unique(df_manager.Manager_name):\n",
    "            \n",
    "            ratios_practical.loc[index,manager]=len(df_manager[(df_manager.Manager_name==manager)&(df_manager.match=='yes')])/len(df_manager[df_manager.Manager_name==manager])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        index=index+1"
   ]
  },

    "# z_score for managers each period\n",
    "z_score_m = (ratios_practical-ratio_m_mean)/ratio_m_std\n",
    "z_score_m.to_csv('z_score_m.csv')\n",
    "# average z_score for managers\n",
    "z_score=z_score_m.mean(skipna=True).to_frame().reset_index().rename(columns={'index':'manager',0:'z_score'})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 475,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# collect the observed ratio and the simulated ratio and z_score for managers\n",
    "ratio_m_m_1 = ratio_m_mean.mean(skipna=True).to_frame().reset_index().rename(columns={'index':'manager',0:'expected'})\n",
    "ratios_1 = ratios_practical.mean(skipna=True).to_frame().reset_index().rename(columns={'index':'manager',0:'practical'})\n",
    "ratio=ratios_1.merge(ratio_m_m_1,how='left',on='manager').merge(z_score,how='left',on='manager')\n",
    "\n",
    "# add the nationality to ratio\n",
    "for man_ in ratio.manager:\n",
    "    index =np.where(ratio.manager ==man_)[0]\n",
    "    ratio.loc[index,'manager_nationality']=manager_info[manager_info.Manager_name==man_].manager_nationality.values[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "ratio.loc[:,'count']=1\n",
    "# sort it by manager nationality\n",
    "ratio=ratio.groupby(['manager_nationality','manager','practical','expected','z_score'])['count'].agg(np.sum).reset_index()#.drop(0,axis=0)"
   ]
  },

    "ratio.to_csv('ratio.csv')"

   ],
   "source": [
    "''' plot the z_score, which we didn't use it PPT but it's a good method to show the difference between observed (practical) value\n",
    "and the simulated (expected) value\n",
    "'''\n",
    "# want to show in nationality wise\n",
    "ratio_1 = ratio.groupby(['manager_nationality'])[['practical','expected','z_score']].agg(np.mean).reset_index()\n",
    "x_axis=np.arange(len(ratio_1))\n",
    "x_label=ratio_1.manager_nationality\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-dark')\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,1,figsize=(10,10),constrained_layout=True)\n",
    "y1=ratio_1.practical\n",
    "y2=ratio_1.expected\n",
    "y3 = ratio_1.z_score\n",
    "lin_0 =ax[0].plot(y1,label='Observed')\n",
    "lin_1 =ax[0].plot(y2,label='Simulated')\n",
    "ax[0].bar(x_label,ratio_1.z_score, color='firebrick',alpha=0.6,label = 'z_score',linestyle='dashed')\n",
    "ax[0].fill_between(x_axis, y2,y1,where=y1 >= y2,color='grey',alpha=0.7, interpolate=True)\n",
    "ax[0].fill_between(x_axis, y2,y1,where=y1 < y2,color='white',alpha=0.7, interpolate=True)\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel('percentage of same nationality')\n",
    "ax[0].set_xticks(x_axis)\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylim(-.2)\n",
    "ax[0].grid(True)\n",
    "ax[0].set_xticklabels(ratio_1.manager_nationality)\n",
    "ax[0].xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90,labelsize=10)\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "ax[0].set_title('Detect homophily of managers')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# want to show in manager wise\n",
    "ratio_1=ratio\n",
    "x_axis=np.arange(len(ratio_1))\n",
    "x_label=ratio_1.manager\n",
    "y1=ratio_1.practical\n",
    "y2=ratio_1.expected\n",
    "y3 = ratio_1.z_score\n",
    "ax[1].plot(x_label,y1,label='Observed')\n",
    "ax[1].plot(y2,label='Simulated')\n",
    "ax[1].fill_between(x_axis, y2,y1,where=y1 >= y2,color='grey',alpha=0.7, interpolate=True)\n",
    "ax[1].fill_between(x_axis, y2,y1,where=y1 < y2,color='white',alpha=0.7, interpolate=True)\n",
    "lin_2 = ax[1].bar(x_label,ratio_1.z_score, color='firebrick',alpha=0.6,label = 'z_score',linestyle='dashed')\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylim(-1)\n",
    "ax[1].xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90,labelsize=8)\n",
    "ax[1].legend()\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel('z_score')\n",
    "ax[1].set_xticks(ticks)\n",
    "ax[1].set_xticklabels(set(ratio.manager_nationality))\n",
    "\n",
    "# color spans\n",
    "x_0=0\n",
    "ticks=[]\n",
    "for n in np.unique(ratio.manager_nationality):\n",
    "    count=np.where(np.unique(ratio.manager_nationality)==n)[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    color = [1-x_1/len(ratio),1,0] if count%2==1 else [x_1/len(ratio),0,1]\n",
    "    x_0 = np.where(ratio.manager_nationality==n)[0][0]-0.35\n",
    "    x_1 = np.where(ratio.manager_nationality==n)[0][-1]+0.35\n",
    "    ax[1].axvspan(x_0, x_1, ymin=0, ymax=1,alpha = 0.1,color = color)\n",
    "    ticks.append(np.where(ratio.manager_nationality==n)[0].mean())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Result corresponding to periods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### mathematical method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 478,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# mathematical method -- calculate the probability that a manager random choose players from the same nationality\n",
    "'''This may not be a good method, it is explained in the begining of the simulation part'''\n",
    "\n",
    "'''\n",
    "df   -- data frame\n",
    "year -- int, specify year\n",
    "transfer_period -- string, 'Winter' or 'Summer'\n",
    "'''\n",
    "def probability(df,year,transfer_period):\n",
    "    df_year = df.loc[(df.year==year)&(df.transfer_period==transfer_period)]\n",
    "    player = df_year.groupby(['player_name','nationality'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "    player=player.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "    manager = df_year.groupby(['Manager_name','manager_nationality'])['count'].agg(np.sum)\n",
    "    manager=manager.to_frame().reset_index()\n",
    "# total is the number of all the posibilities of choice\n",
    "    total = len(manager)*len(player)\n",
    "    pl_na = player.nationality.value_counts()\n",
    "    mn_na = manager.manager_nationality.value_counts()\n",
    "    num_same=0\n",
    "# num_same is the number of posibilities of choosing players from the same nationality\n",
    "    for i in mn_na.keys():\n",
    "        if i in pl_na.keys():\n",
    "            num_same=num_same+pl_na.get(i)*mn_na.get(i)\n",
    "# get the expected percentage of managers choosing players from the same nationality\n",
    "    expected = num_same/total\n",
    "    return expected"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 479,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# expected percentage of a manager random choose players from the same nationality\n",
    "# for with England and without England\n",
    "math=[]\n",
    "math_without=[]\n",
    "df_in_wo = df_in[df_in.manager_nationality!='England']\n",
    "for year in np.arange(min(df.year),2021):\n",
    "    for transfer_period in ['Summer','Winter']:\n",
    "        math.append(probability(df_in,year,transfer_period))\n",
    "        math_without.append(probability(df_in_wo,year,transfer_period))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "result.set_index('time')\n",
    "result.to_csv('result.csv')"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Robustness test to show if the observed values and simulated values are different"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### chi_square test -- difference in distribution across transfer periods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 483,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "p value is 1.0\n",
      "Independent (H0 holds true)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# chi_square test for with England\n",
    "data = result.loc[result.expected!=0,['expected','with_en']]\n",
    "stat, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(data.expected,data.with_en) \n",
    "  \n",
    "# interpret p-value \n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "print(\"p value is \" + str(p)) \n",
    "if p <= alpha: \n",
    "    print('Dependent (reject H0)') \n",
    "else: \n",
    "    print('Independent (H0 holds true)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 484,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "p value is 1.0\n",
      "Independent (H0 holds true)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# chi_square test for without England\n",
    "data = result.loc[result.expected_without!=0,['expected_without','without_En']]\n",
    "stat, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(data.expected_without,data.without_En) \n",
    "  \n",
    "# interpret p-value \n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "print(\"p value is \" + str(p)) \n",
    "if p <= alpha: \n",
    "    print('Dependent (reject H0)') \n",
    "else: \n",
    "    print('Independent (H0 holds true)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### t-test -- difference in means"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},

     "data": {

     },
     "execution_count": 485,

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#two tailed test, but we need to use one tailed test, just divide pvalue by 2\n",
    "stats.ttest_ind(result.expected,result.with_en)"
   ]
  },

    "# network graph\n",
    "g = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(df6, 'Manager_name', 'player_name')\n",
    "\n",
    "hubs = list(df['Manager_name'].drop_duplicates())\n",
    "\n",
    "hubs2 = list(df['player_name'])\n",
    "\n",
    "labels = {}    \n",
    "for node in g.nodes():\n",
    "    if node in hubs:\n",
    "        #set the node name as the key and the label as its value \n",
    "        labels[node] = node\n",
    "\n",
    "edges = {}    \n",
    "for node in g.nodes():\n",
    "    if node in hubs2:\n",
    "        ('red')\n",
    "    else: \n",
    "        ('black') \n",
    "        #set the node name as the key and the label as its value \n",
    "        edges[node] = node\n",
    "\n",
    "color_map = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for node in g.nodes:\n",
    "    if node in hubs2:\n",
    "        color_map.append('lightcoral')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        color_map.append('slategray')\n",
    "        \n",
    "betCent = nx.degree_centrality(g)\n",
    "\n",
    "node_size =  [v * 7000 for v in betCent.values()]\n",
    "\n",
    "pos = nx.spring_layout(g)\n",
    "\n",
    "nx.draw_networkx(g, pos, with_labels = True, labels = labels, edge_color = color_map, node_color='royalblue',alpha = 1, width = 0.5, node_size = node_size, font_size = 7.5)\n",
    "plt.style.use('fivethirtyeight')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (25,10)\n",
    "plt.savefig('homograph.png')\n"

    "##  Minutes played by signings"

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x800 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the example planets dataset\n",
    "planets = bot\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the orbital period with horizontal boxes\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x=\"Min\", y=\"Manager_name\", data=bot.sort_values(\"practical\"),\n",
    "            whis=[0, 100], width=.3, palette=\"Reds\", hue='match')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add in points to show each observation\n",
    "sns.stripplot(x=\"Min\", y=\"Manager_name\", data=bot.sort_values(\"practical\"),\n",
    "              size=3, linewidth=0, hue='match', palette='Greys')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.yaxis.grid(False)\n",
    "ax.set(ylabel=\"\")\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel=\"Minutes Played\", ylabel = \"Manager Name\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title('Minutes Played by Signings for non CL Clubs', fontsize=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend(loc='lower left',\n",
    "bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0),\n",
    "ncol=1, title='Matching Nationality')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Minutes Played\", fontsize=15)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Manager Name\", fontsize=15)\n",
    "sns.despine()\n",
    "# Tweak the visual presentation\n",
    "ax.xaxis.grid(False)\n",
    "plt.savefig('Minutes played Bot.png')"
   ]
